From: pestopoppa <https://github.com/ikawrakow/ik_llama.cpp/pull/1744#issuecomment-4388461824>
Subject: [PATCH] Silence "Oops: tensor with strange name mtp_*.weight" warnings

PR #1744 introduces two non-`blk.*` top-level tensors (`mtp_pre_proj.weight`,
`mtp_post_proj.weight`) which the size-accounting iteration at
`src/llama.cpp:2509` doesn't recognize. Cosmetic but noisy.

Defensive: also covers `mtp_centroids` / `mtp_token_ordering` which are
TENSOR_NOT_REQUIRED in `create_gemma4_mtp_tensors` (absent from current
Q8_0/F16 drafters, may appear in future variants).

Verified on top of 0f728f380 + the params_use_gemma4_external_mtp fix:
"Oops: ... mtp_post_proj.weight" / "Oops: ... mtp_pre_proj.weight" both gone.

---
 src/llama.cpp | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/llama.cpp b/src/llama.cpp
@@ -2504,6 +2504,12 @@
         if (name == "output_norm.weight") {
             continue;
         }
+        // Top-level (non-blk.*) tensors introduced by Gemma4Assistant (gemma4_mtp arch).
+        // Loaded by create_gemma4_mtp_tensors; not per-layer, so they don't participate in this accounting.
+        if (name == "mtp_pre_proj.weight" || name == "mtp_post_proj.weight" ||
+            name == "mtp_centroids.weight" || name == "mtp_token_ordering.weight") {
+            continue;
+        }
         auto pos = name.find("blk.");
         if (pos != 0) {
             LLAMA_LOG_WARN("Oops: tensor with strange name %s\n", name.c_str());
